'''Osteoporosis''' is the weakening of [[bone]]s in the body. It is caused by lack of [[calcium]] deposited in the bones. This lack of [[calcium]] causes the bones to become brittle, so they break easily. Some side effects are limping. Some symptoms late in the disease include pain in the bones, living in a [[wheelchair]] (as a result of), and lower back pain due to [[Spine|spinal bone]] fractures.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://health.google.com/health/ref/Osteoporosis |title=Google Health - Osteoporosis |accessdate=2009-11-16 |last= |first= |coauthors= |date= |format= |work= |publisher=Google/A.D.A.M. |pages= |quote= }}</ref> Elderly people are more likely to develop osteoporosis than younger people.  The amount of calcium in the bones decreases as a person gets older.

